                <h2 id="parent-5">Money</h2><br>
                <h2 class="h2_height">Q: What is “Buff”?</h2>
                <p class="textcolor">
                    A: “Buff” is a virtual currency used on E-Pal, it can be used to pay for services and tips.
                    1.00 Buff = 1.00 USD; “Buff balance” is the remaining deposit on your account that is able to be used.
                    The money in “Buff balance” is a non-withdrawable currency that can only be spent on E-Pal.
                </p><br>
                <p class="textcolor">
                    “Buff income” refers to the income you have generated through providing services and collecting tips.
                    Income can be withdrawn and
                    “Withdrawable Buff” is the number of Buff that are available to be withdrawn.
                </p><br>
                <h2 class="h2_height">Q:  What is “E-Coin”?</h2>
                <p class="textcolor">
                    A: “E-Coin” is also a virtual currency used on E-Pal. It is used to send gifts in “Team Room” and through our IM messenger. E-coin does not need to be recharged, as it is automatically converted from Buff; 1.00 Buff = 100.00 E-Coins; “E-Coin income” refers to the accumulated income from the gifts you receive through
                    “Team Room” and IM messenger, which can be withdrawn.
                </p><br>
                <h2 class="h2_height">Q:  Can I recharge through other methods?</h2>
